task.summary: Created CSVRecord and Reader classes (not yet implemented or fully decleared)
Corrected cmakelists.txt and added clion data.

Added Dictionary to facilitate adding Tweets and breaking them down into tokens. This includes: - Dictionary: Class stores a list of DictionaryEntry's as well and facilitates adding new Entry's - DictionaryEntry: A term in the dictionary. Can be expressed either as a regex or a literal string. - StringUtils: Class with static functions used for string utilities. Currently only trim.
Created test of Dictionary. First test resulted in 2756 terms. This will end up being an... Interesting problem.
Added code to display all terms and group user handles and URL's into a single category.

Created TweetLoader, that can load in TwitterData from a CSV file with a preset format and store into a large vector. Currently only does that. In the future, it will also make use of the twokenizer sh script to convert into tokens.
Added a maximum number of processing threads that can run at a given time, to avoid overloading the system in forks but to still be able to split up the task into small (600 tweet-long) subtasks.
Implemented a faster HashMap implementation for the dictionary to allow for faster insertion and lookup
Added a configuration file with an open source json readers. Defaults to reading to config/config.json. Implemented as a singleton pattern to facilitate global usage.
Removed all string literals that can be transfered to the config.json file.
Fixed CWD error in configuration class.
Added task size and max threads to tweet loader.
Added output generator to create output to file.
Miscelaneous bug fixes as well as caching of indexes in DictionaryEntry.
